The paper proposes a novel method for personalized session-based recommendation using graph neural networks and attention mechanism. The main focus of the paper is on machine learning and artificial intelligence techniques for recommendation systems, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of natural language processing techniques, which could place it in the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with information retrieval and recommendation systems, which could place it in the cs.IR (Information Retrieval) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of real-world datasets, which could place it in the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-category.
